defaultBIS Sustainability Committeedefault&#xa0;
defaultThe following terms of reference were signed off by the BIS Operations Committee at the beginning of August 2013 and issued following a the first meeting of the Sustainability Committee at the beginning of September 2013. 
default&#xa0;
defaultRemitdefaultThe purpose of the Sustainability Committee is to support the Executive Board in providing leadership, co-ordination and guidance to BIS in fulfilling the Department’s sustainability commitments as set out in the Business Plan and Greening Government commitments and embedding sustainability principles in BIS policy making.
default&#xa0;
defaultThe Director General Finance and Commercial is accountable to the Executive Board for the Department’s sustainability performance, supported by the Board appointed Sustainability Champion. The Committee reports to the Executive Board through the Operations Committee, who act on behalf of the Executive Board. 
default&#xa0;
defaultThe Department’s sustainability commitments fall under three themes: policy, operations and procurement. Each of these themes is represented through SCS level membership on the Committee. The Committee also has representation from the voluntary BIS Green Guardians network.
default&#xa0;defaultDefinition of SustainabilitydefaultSustainable development means encouraging economic growth while protecting the environment and improving our quality of life - all without affecting the ability of future generations to do the same. 
defaultThe Sustainability Committee will oversee how BIS takes account of sustainable development as a part of how it develops its policies, how it runs its operations and how it buys its goods and services. 
defaultTaking account of sustainability in policy making includes considering environmental, social and economic impact of policy. Achieving sustainability also includes policies that contribute to economic rebalancing – across sectors and places, moving to a low carbon economy, climate change mitigation and adaptation, disaster resilience, and resource efficiency.
default&#xa0;defaultMembershipdefaultBIS Sustainability Champion (Chair)
defaultDG Finance and Commercial (Board Sponsor)
